    public class Event4AsyncAdapter<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Event4AsyncDelegate<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4>
    The Event4AsyncAdapter is class that adapts an Event4Delegate to Event4AsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously. All asynchronous event distributions are executed in another thread. The Executor to use for the asynchronous event distributions can be chosen during creation of this helper. If no explicit executor is given the a default executor is used. The default executor can be set using the AsyncExecutor.setDefaultExecutor(Executor) property or is created automatically by the AsyncExecutor.
    Author:
    tilmann
